{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"totalCount":17,"edges":[{"node":{"id":"d65ebb41-ac32-512b-9c79-45b03a6950c5","frontmatter":{"linkURL":"https://www.instagram.com/nicemarcela/","instaURL":"https://www.instagram.com/agrowinggirl333/","title":"Tyanna Braswell — Growing natural hair after shaving for 6 years: \"My hair will grow again, and so will I.\"","type":"Hair Type: 3A/3B/3C","date":"Apr 10th 2021","product1":{"title":"Cleansing","description":"Dr. Bronners Lavender Castile Soap. I dillute and use the shampoo way — ½ Tbsp. in your hand, worked into wet hair, or dilute ½ Tbsp. in ½ a cup of water and work that into wet hair.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/10ec2d7fb9e70d4f4d7e80ee1548cf6e/drbronnershampoo.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://shop.drbronner.com/products/lavender-pure-castile-liquid-soap"}]},"product2":{"title":"Conditioning","description":"Shea moisture curl and shine conditioner.  Sometimes I only halfway rinse it out of my hair if I am planning to do a slicked hairstyle or something.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/75a603552140295e974c9df5de717423/sheamoistureconditioner.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.walmart.com/ip/SheaMoisture-Curl-and-Shine-Conditioner-to-Restore-and-Smooth-Dry-Hair-for-Thick-Curly-Hair-13-oz/48319862"}]},"product3":{"title":"Styling","description":"I like to let my hair air dry and I scrunch it every 20 minutes or so. Also if I am in a rush, I turn on the heater in my car and it somewhat acts as a diffuser.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/75a603552140295e974c9df5de717423/sheamoistureconditioner.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.walmart.com/ip/SheaMoisture-Curl-and-Shine-Conditioner-to-Restore-and-Smooth-Dry-Hair-for-Thick-Curly-Hair-13-oz/48319862"}]},"instagrammer":"@agrowinggirl333","author":"@nicemarcela","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/bd6d9cbafba8785784e0a7c662b7e8cd/ee604/tee2.png","srcSet":"/static/bd6d9cbafba8785784e0a7c662b7e8cd/69585/tee2.png 200w,\n/static/bd6d9cbafba8785784e0a7c662b7e8cd/497c6/tee2.png 400w,\n/static/bd6d9cbafba8785784e0a7c662b7e8cd/ee604/tee2.png 800w,\n/static/bd6d9cbafba8785784e0a7c662b7e8cd/05d05/tee2.png 1080w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"tyanna-braswell-growing-natural-hair-after-shaving-for-6-years-my-hair-will-grow-again-and-so-will-i"},"excerpt":"She can be seen as a strong, bold woman on her Instagram, where she shares her bad-ass looks with different hairstyles, and her journey of…"}},{"node":{"id":"a6312d84-f201-5721-a262-0981c8b1af7d","frontmatter":{"linkURL":"https://www.instagram.com/nicemarcela/","instaURL":"https://www.instagram.com/beyond_texture/","title":"Talking Beyond Texture with curl specialist, Jessica Knight.","type":"Hair Type: 3A/3B","date":"Mar 27th 2021","product1":{"title":"Cleansing","description":"I alternate between AG Hair Balance and Innersense Hairbath 2-3x a week. Once or twice a month I may use a clarifier and choose Malibu C Wellness UnDo Goo! I always cleanse anytime I wash and if I need an extra cleanse I will do two cleanses back to back. If I am feeling really \"treat myself\" I will use a scalp scrub like Innersense Enlightenment. I apply my cleanser directly to my scalp and scrub while feeding it water to help move the product down my length.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/a5194ebdbcac4009c264d24ae01ce939/agshampoo.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.amazon.com/AG-Natural-Balance-Vinegar-Sulfate-Free/dp/B073GQJ1DW"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/0ab92f0759fba90cf27d4b7a7342c4a0/innersensehairbath.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.walmart.com/ip/Innersense-Organic-Beauty-Hydrating-Hairbath-10-oz/900609896"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/8dc9975e27088a73239d080919f5cdcd/malibushampoo.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.amazon.com/Malibu-Do-Goo-Shampoo-fl-oz/dp/B0741BYML6/ref=sr_1_5?dchild=1&keywords=Malibu+C+Wellness+UnDo+Goo%21&qid=1616861752&sr=8-5"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/204ff91c303357934eb2bc83df8fefc7/innersensescalpscrub.jpg"},"productURL":"https://innersensebeauty.com/product/scalp-scrub/"}]},"product2":{"title":"Conditioning","description":"Condition with Intention! I apply the conditioner of choice. (AG Hair Boost or Innersense Hydrating Cream Conditioner) and feed water into my curls to extend the conditioner as I detangle with my fingers. If I ever run into tangles, I isolate the subsection and smooth or \"milk\" my conditioner and water through the curls from the bottom up to release the tangles. I know I am done detangling when my curls are tangle free, ribbon-y smooth, silky and saturated. I rinse away all my conditioner.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/7aaba7c8aee9bbd2f2a3a32ba5b45821/agconditioner.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.walmart.com/ip/Boost-Apple-Cider-Vinegar-Conditioner/618762446"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/85fe3abe5a5ad9d5472897248dcb6dc7/innersenseconditioner.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.walmart.com/ip/Innersense-Organic-Beauty-Hydrating-Cream-Conditioner-2-oz/785396753"}]},"product3":{"title":"Styling","description":"While still in the shower and using the water that is still in my hair, I layer on my products of choice. In the winter, I am loving Uncle Funkys Daughter Curly Magic, Innersense Inner Peace, Innersense I Create Hold, and The Doux Mousse Def. In the summer I will add in I create Volume instead of the Inner Peace.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/849bbd0a3bd1060f98f95e55aa245070/unclefunkycurlymagic.jpeg"},"productURL":"https://www.walmart.com/ip/Curly-Magic-Curl-Stimulator-12Oz-By-Uncle-Funky-S-Daughter/248487793"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/4a3098f813ffbd130e08ce960ddfdfd1/innersenseinnerpeace.jpg"},"productURL":"https://innersensebeauty.com/product/inner-peace/"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/8568625b1a16c5be2a5ad80bc2325c33/icreateholdinnersense.jpg"},"productURL":"https://innersensebeauty.com/product/i-create-hold/"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/73cdbb394705c40ab2ac5450dfc5dc70/thedouxmousse.png"},"productURL":"https://thedoux.com/products/mousse-def-texture-foam"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/df64613386805b30fb09f6c542690822/icreatevolumeinnersense.jpg"},"productURL":"https://innersensebeauty.com/product/i-create-volume/"}]},"instagrammer":"@beyond_texture","author":"@nicemarcela","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/8a02659e18d80f37f526907c5f790754/ee604/jessicaknight.png","srcSet":"/static/8a02659e18d80f37f526907c5f790754/69585/jessicaknight.png 200w,\n/static/8a02659e18d80f37f526907c5f790754/497c6/jessicaknight.png 400w,\n/static/8a02659e18d80f37f526907c5f790754/ee604/jessicaknight.png 800w,\n/static/8a02659e18d80f37f526907c5f790754/05d05/jessicaknight.png 1080w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"talking-beyond-texture-with-curl-specialist-jessica-knight"},"excerpt":"Jessica Knight is a curl specialist from Kansas, who moved to NYC about six years ago to chase crazy curly dreams. She describes herself as…"}},{"node":{"id":"ef613e89-9c78-5ff9-bcd7-9cbb4c864176","frontmatter":{"linkURL":"https://www.instagram.com/nicemarcela/","instaURL":"https://www.instagram.com/elikiacardot/","title":"Elikia Cardot on her minimalist routine: The best way to get to know your hair.","type":"Hair Type: 3A/3B/3C","date":"Mar 20th 2021","product1":{"title":"Cleansing","description":"My routine is very simple, my hair is not too demanding so I would usually go with a natural plant-based shampoo from Love Beauty and Planet.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/927a5daa4d6d10d2695f275e31ab47c1/lovebeautyandplanetshampoo.png"},"productURL":"https://www.amazon.com/Love-Beauty-Planet-Coconut-Definition/dp/B07YJYXN4V/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1685EX4SXMUZE&dchild=1&keywords=love+beauty+and+planet+shampoo+coconut+milk+and+jasmine&qid=1616246352&sprefix=love+beauty+and+planet+shampoo+coc%2Caps%2C292&sr=8-1"}]},"product2":{"title":"Conditioning","description":"Again for conditioning, there is really just one step. I use the shea moisture deep conditioner, leave it on for 5-10 minutes, and wash it off.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/3152b7eb9bd5a7818e44f6e6bbc14ca3/sheamoistureDC.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.amazon.com/SheaMoisture-Shea-Butter-Treatment-Masque/dp/B0118QDDCQ/ref=sr_1_5?crid=1HW53RKIPCF7R&dchild=1&keywords=shea+moisture+deep+treatment+masque&qid=1616246388&sprefix=shea+moisture+dee%2Caps%2C272&sr=8-5"}]},"product3":{"title":"Styling","description":"On damp hair I detangle with a comb, apply Bouclème curl cream and a bit of coconut oil, and let it air dry.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/0f5bf32ce58be19b91622e95ed73be0a/bouclemecream.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.amazon.com/Boucleme-Cream-Natural-Styling-Cream/dp/B01N6EWJM9/ref=sr_1_3?dchild=1&keywords=boucleme+curl+cream&qid=1616246421&sr=8-3"}]},"instagrammer":"@elikiacardot","author":"@nicemarcela","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/6536b967edc970886463ce463f79ca41/ee604/elikia.png","srcSet":"/static/6536b967edc970886463ce463f79ca41/69585/elikia.png 200w,\n/static/6536b967edc970886463ce463f79ca41/497c6/elikia.png 400w,\n/static/6536b967edc970886463ce463f79ca41/ee604/elikia.png 800w,\n/static/6536b967edc970886463ce463f79ca41/05d05/elikia.png 1080w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"elikia-cardot-on-her-minimalist-routine-the-best-way-to-get-to-know-your-hair"},"excerpt":"Elikia is an interior designer and property stylist based in Sydney. She grew up and spent most of her childhood in Gabon, Africa then moved…"}},{"node":{"id":"69f17294-db72-564c-b1b6-431e2c264e54","frontmatter":{"linkURL":"https://www.instagram.com/nicemarcela/","instaURL":"https://www.instagram.com/themichellesingleton/","title":"Michelle Singleton, CEO of Her Place Is In, about the future of her project, and personal goals in plant medicine.","type":"Hair Type: 3A/3B/3C","date":"Mar 13th 2021","product1":{"title":"Cleansing","description":"Cleansing always feels like a happy dance for my scalp. I am currently on my 2nd bottle of Pattern Beauty Hydrating Shampoo and so far I love it except for how slippery/watery it feels coming out of the bottle. I like to prep my hair with conditioner (especially if my curls have matted from friction from the collar of my clothes or sleep). I am currently using \"As I am\" Coconut co-wash to prep and get the hair moisturized. I lightly rinse then apply the shampoo and rinse. ","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/87d2797bee219441cad572b14cc3cc5a/coconutcowash.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.amazon.com/Am-Coconut-Cowash-Cleansing-Conditioner/dp/B00641UCY8"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/c6287ac77151ecc09968a68888ca2f64/patternhydrationshampoo.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.patternbeauty.com/products/hydration-shampoo"}]},"product2":{"title":"Conditioning","description":"I apply Pattern Beauty Leave-in conditioner, I actually do not use a traditional conditioner. It is always a leave-in! Depending on what my hair feels like, I like to do two applications of a leave-in conditioner after the cleanse and use my hands to squeeze out the excess. This is preparation for my styling.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/5a5ab194ae8d49774d74fd57f34198ab/patternleavein.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.patternbeauty.com/products/leave-in"}]},"product3":{"title":"Styling","description":"Step 1: Leave-in conditioner is a huge part of my styling process. I use Pattern Beauty best selling leave-in conditioner. I do not know why I waited so long to do the float test to figure out my hair porosity. I actually always knew I was really dry ie. skin & hair, so I assumed my hair just needed more assistance with moisture. My hair type might be viewed as high porosity but it is in fact low porosity - Low porosity hair repels moisture when you try to wet it and is hard to process since it resists penetration of chemicals. It is important for me to use a cream first and then apply an oil to help lock in moisture. Step 2: I apply Avocurl Daily Moisturizer after my leave-in, it is an AHHmazing product, made with aloe and avocado which my hair is a big fan of! Final step and Pro tip for long haired curlies: After styling and while your hair is still damp put it in a traditional bonnet, the bonnet holding the hair in and the drying process overnight will give you the same if not better bounce. This is perfect for me because my hair has lost all its layers and curlies need shape to highlight our crown and gorgeous faces! I also use a wide-tooth comb to detangle my curls. I also LOVE a good baby hair swirl or just let them live and do their own thing. I have been using Pattern Beauty \"toothbrush\" styling tool for a couple of months now and my baby hairs really appreciate the support.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/5a5ab194ae8d49774d74fd57f34198ab/patternleavein.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.patternbeauty.com/products/leave-in"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/8ed9b33e55ebad660311f2add834cde8/avocurlmoisturizer.png"},"productURL":"https://www.avocurl.com/products/avocurl-daily-moisturizer"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/f9351bb39538e7c1c294e23e301dca9b/patternedgetool.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.patternbeauty.com/products/edge-tool"}]},"instagrammer":"@themichellesingleton","author":"@nicemarcela","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/177329ae578e23a8dd63d16e5ef24a73/ee604/michellesingleton.png","srcSet":"/static/177329ae578e23a8dd63d16e5ef24a73/69585/michellesingleton.png 200w,\n/static/177329ae578e23a8dd63d16e5ef24a73/497c6/michellesingleton.png 400w,\n/static/177329ae578e23a8dd63d16e5ef24a73/ee604/michellesingleton.png 800w,\n/static/177329ae578e23a8dd63d16e5ef24a73/05d05/michellesingleton.png 1080w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"michelle-singleton-ceo-of-her-place-is-in-about-the-future-of-her-project-and-personal-goals-in-plant-medicine"},"excerpt":"Michelle is a true force of nature, who speaks up for what she believes in, and follows through with action. She describes herself as a…"}},{"node":{"id":"3ff7f73b-8220-5417-a028-319e3531a341","frontmatter":{"linkURL":"https://www.instagram.com/nicemarcela/","instaURL":"https://www.instagram.com/verooobonilla/","title":"Veronica Bonilla, the creator of VEROBONITA, on her relationship with style, and haircare for dyed hair.","type":"Hair Type: 3A/3B/3C","date":"Mar 6th 2021","product1":{"title":"Cleansing","description":"I like to pre-poo my hair with the Briogeo Scalp Revival before I shampoo my roots with a massage scalp tool for 5 mins to get all the product buildup out. Once I am done with that I like to use the Olaplex shampoo to give my hair the moisture it needs.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/4dfd369c0b30f09932ba174b07d4ef7d/briogeoshampoo.png"},"productURL":"https://briogeohair.com/products/scalp-revival-charcoal-coconut-oil-micro-exfoliating-shampoo"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/2adf96c61970a3b329f31f5ff0ba4564/olaplex4.png"},"productURL":"https://www.olaplex.com/products/no-4-bond-maintenance-shampoo-1"}]},"product2":{"title":"Conditioning","description":"For conditioning I like to use the Olaplex conditioner. I leave it on my hair for 10 mins and finger tangle my hair after the 10 mins before rinsing it off. After my wash I like to do a deep conditioning mask for 30-45 mins.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/4fa468e8cf2e102229423b0a11deb707/olaplex5.png"},"productURL":"https://www.olaplex.com/products/no-5-bond-maintenance-conditioner"}]},"product3":{"title":"Styling","description":"I start with massaging oil on my scalp, right now I am using argan oil. Follow by the No.6 leave-in from Olaplex, follow by my styling cream from emerge and gel. I like to apply my products raking and scrunching it.","gallery":[{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/422bb66302bd00d9e995a9fb1d9614d6/olaplex6.jpg"},"productURL":"https://www.olaplex.com/products/no-6-bond-smoother"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/b81bf68bedb959b76c1b3a91792f8ed6/emergecream.png"},"productURL":"https://www.emergebeautiful.com/us/en/our-products/cream/the-works-butter-cream-15-fl-oz.html"},{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/a00f812756629c5816f41a0631987532/emergegel.png"},"productURL":"https://www.emergebeautiful.com/us/en/our-products/gel/style-goals-gel.html"}]},"instagrammer":"@verooobonilla","author":"@nicemarcela","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/36d74795a0c32ff09f719b5831e48067/ee604/verobonilla.png","srcSet":"/static/36d74795a0c32ff09f719b5831e48067/69585/verobonilla.png 200w,\n/static/36d74795a0c32ff09f719b5831e48067/497c6/verobonilla.png 400w,\n/static/36d74795a0c32ff09f719b5831e48067/ee604/verobonilla.png 800w,\n/static/36d74795a0c32ff09f719b5831e48067/05d05/verobonilla.png 1080w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"veronica-bonilla-the-creator-of-verobonita-on-her-relationship-with-style-and-haircare-for-dyed-hair"},"excerpt":"Veronica Bonilla is a creative, blogger and entrepreneur from Brooklyn. As an Afro-Latina woman, she advocates for the Black community…"}}]}}}